action.text:
The data doesn't lie: physical inactivity kills at the same rate as smoking, heart disease, and diabetes. Yet resistance training remains criminally undervalued.

@foundmyfitness recently testified before the Senate Aging Committee, delivering a wake-up call backed by hard science. The muscle loss statistics alone are staggering - 10% gone by age 50, up to 40% by 70 for many Americans.

But here's what matters most: higher muscle mass slashes mortality risk by 30% through improved insulin sensitivity. Grip strength outperforms blood pressure as a cardiovascular death predictor. The strongest middle-aged adults cut their dementia risk by 42%.

This testimony before @senateaging, made possible by Senator Rick Scott (@flsenrickscott), reframes resistance training from optional fitness activity to essential medical intervention - our most powerful weapon against aging, period.

Full testimony with Q&A now live on the FoundMyFitness YouTube channel.

#longevity #healthspan #aging #resistancetraining #musclemass #fitness #science #health #wellness #preventivemedicine
